01:37:04,952 --> 01:37:06,180
Harold.

972
01:37:06,512 --> 01:37:07,946
How unexpected.

973
01:38:11,557 --> 01:38:12,673
Harold call it off!

974
01:38:13,798 --> 01:38:15,197
You can't do it.

975
01:38:15,518 --> 01:38:17,270
You can't deal with these people.

976
01:38:17,799 --> 01:38:20,711
For Christ sake, they're not interested in money.
They're political, they're fanatics!

977
01:38:22,039 --> 01:38:23,437
Come on, George.

978
01:38:36,239 --> 01:38:37,593
Come in.

979
01:38:42,721 --> 01:38:44,871
O'Flaherty, Harold Shand.

980
01:38:46,801 --> 01:38:48,837
There's 60 grand here.

981
01:38:50,361 --> 01:38:53,957
- To make sure there's no more hard feelings.
- Gonna have to wait and see the boss about that.

982
01:38:54,402 --> 01:38:55,551
Where is he?

983
01:38:55,801 --> 01:38:58,362
He's out there. Last race.

984
01:38:58,722 --> 01:39:00,041
He'll be back in a minute.

985
01:40:21,289 --> 01:40:22,961
This is Mr. Shand.

986
01:40:23,490 --> 01:40:25,958
He's brought the money and he wants an answer.

987
01:40:29,370 --> 01:40:32,567
- How much is that?
- 60 grand, it's in the case.

988
01:40:33,531 --> 01:40:34,929
You'd better count it.

989
01:40:36,850 --> 01:40:38,603
If you don't mind, I will.

990
01:41:51,977 --> 01:41:54,048
You wait here, I'll got and get them,
I won't be a minute

991
01:41:58,857 --> 01:42:00,734
Mr. Restivo?

992
01:42:16,099 --> 01:42:17,374
Where's Charlie?

993
01:42:19,220 --> 01:42:20,811
Everything's alright.

994
01:42:21,259 --> 01:42:23,296
All the troubles are over.

995
01:42:23,779 --> 01:42:25,099
What did he say?

996
01:42:26,660 --> 01:42:28,059
Sorry, Harold.

997
01:42:28,421 --> 01:42:31,777
But I'm glad you dropped in to say
goodbye, that's real nice.

998
01:42:32,580 --> 01:42:34,457
- What are you leaving?
- Yeah.

999
01:42:34,741 --> 01:42:37,255
- You're not going back to New York?
- Next flight out.

1000
01:42:38,541 --> 01:42:40,213
Come on, Charlie

1001
01:42:40,462 --> 01:42:43,454
I know we've had a few problems, we've only
been here a couple of days.

1002
01:42:43,742 --> 01:42:48,258
Yeah a couple of days that turned out to be
another St. Valentines Massacre.

1003
01:42:48,502 --> 01:42:51,096
But that settled it, once and for all.

1004
01:42:52,622 --> 01:42:57,377
Yes, I'd like a porter to suite 513 please,
and we'd like a cab right away.

1005
01:42:57,903 --> 01:42:59,336
Thank you.

1006
01:43:00,382 --> 01:43:02,453
You two can't wait to get out of here, can you?

1007
01:43:02,823 --> 01:43:06,259
I always react like that to bombs blowing up, mass murders...

1008
01:43:06,944 --> 01:43:08,263
It's a hang-up of mine.

1009
01:43:09,983 --> 01:43:13,693
It's coming to something when the Mafia
can't handle a little problem, innit?

1010
01:43:13,944 --> 01:43:15,263
A little problem?

1011
01:43:15,504 --> 01:43:17,461
Tony did you hear what he said?
A little problem...

1012
01:43:18,065 --> 01:43:20,738
This is like a bad night in Vietnam

1013
01:43:21,105 --> 01:43:23,460
But it's over, I've pulled the plug on 'em.

1014
01:43:23,785 --> 01:43:26,015
We do not deal with gangsters, period.

1015
01:43:26,905 --> 01:43:30,535
This country is a worse risk than Cuba was.
It's a banana republic.

1016
01:43:31,105 --> 01:43:32,380
You're a mess.

1017
01:43:33,626 --> 01:43:34,853
Ciao, Harold.

1018
01:43:37,906 --> 01:43:39,260
Bon voyage then.

1019
01:43:47,267 --> 01:43:48,541
I'll tell you something...

1020
01:43:51,387 --> 01:43:55,381
I'm glad I found out in time just what a partnership
with a pair of wankers like you would've been.

1021
01:43:56,548 --> 01:43:58,983
A sleeping partner's one thing,
but you're in a fucking coma!

1022
01:43:59,868 --> 01:44:02,826
No wonder you got an energy crisis
your side of the water!

1023
01:44:03,228 --> 01:44:07,380
But us British, we're used to a bit more
vitality, imagination,

1024
01:44:07,909 --> 01:44:09,900
touch of the Dunkirk spirit, know what I mean?

1025
01:44:12,269 --> 01:44:14,305
The days when Yanks could come over 'ere...

1026
01:44:14,550 --> 01:44:16,188
and buy up Nelson's Column...

1027
01:44:16,430 --> 01:44:20,105
an 'arley street surgeon and a couple'a Windmill
Girls are definitely over!

1028
01:44:20,591 --> 01:44:23,503
- Now look...
- Shut up you long streak of paralysed piss.

1029
01:44:27,031 --> 01:44:30,341
What I'm looking for is someone who can contribute

1030
01:44:31,711 --> 01:44:34,305
to what England has given to the world:

1031
01:44:34,832 --> 01:44:40,782
culture, sophistication, genius. A little bit more
than an 'ot dog, know what I mean?

1032
01:44:43,472 --> 01:44:47,227
We're in the Common Market now, a
and my new deal is with Europe,

1033
01:44:48,673 --> 01:44:53,383
I'm going into partnership with a German
organisation. Yeah! The Krauts!

1034
01:44:53,792 --> 01:44:58,390
they've got ambition, know-how,
and they don't lose their bottle.

1035
01:45:00,074 --> 01:45:01,587
Look at you...

1036
01:45:02,674 --> 01:45:04,072
The Mafia?

1037
01:45:04,793 --> 01:45:06,386
I've shit 'em.

1038
01:45:33,076 --> 01:45:34,556
Hey hold up, where's Victoria?